@heading Basic

@defvr {Setting} use_nanocfg Enable Nano Config
This master switch will make @b{BashStyle-NG} adjust the settings of @code{nano}.
@end defvr

@defvr {Setting} nano_backup Backup files
If enabled backup files to @code{filename~} upon save.
@end defvr

@defvr {Setting} show_position Display position of cursor
If enabled show the current position (line, column) in the minibar (or if
disabled, the traditional status bar)
@end defvr

@defvr {Setting} history Use search-string history
If enabled save searches for future reuse in a history.
@end defvr

@defvr {Setting} minibar Enable Minibar
Enable the minibar introduced in GNU Nano 5.0, instead of the traditional
status bar.
@end defvr

@defvr {Setting} line_numbers Show line numbers
If enabled the line numbers are displayed.
@end defvr

@heading Editing

@defvr {Setting} auto_indent Enable auto-indention
If enabled the file is auto indented, based on the determined filetype.
@end defvr

@defvr {Setting} syntax_highlight Enable syntax highlighting
If enabled syntax highlighting, based on the determined filetype, will be done.
@end defvr

@defvr {Setting} hide_help Hide shortcuts
If enabled the keyboard shortcuts/help at the bottom will be hidden.
@end defvr

@defvr {Setting} case_sensitive Search case-sensitively
If enabled, searches are performed case-sensitive.
@end defvr

@defvr {Setting} no_wrap No line wrapping
If enabled, long lines will be scrolled horizontally, instead of being wrapped.
@end defvr

@defvr {Setting} tab_to_spaces Convert tab to spaces
If enabled, tabs wille be converted to spaces.
@end defvr

@defvr {Setting} tab_size Tab width
Set the width of a tab in spaces
@end defvr

@defvr {Setting} guide_stripe Guide Stripe Position
The position (in characters) the stripe is displayed, indicating overlong lines.
@end defvr

@heading UI Colors

@defvr {Setting} set_uicolors
Enable custom user interface coloring, if disabled the following settings wille
be ignored.
@end defvr

@defvr {Setting} bold_text Use bold text
Will make text of some UI elements forcibly bold, even if non-bold colors are
selected by the user.
@end defvr

The following settings allow to color all UI elements of GNU Nano, separately
for text color and background color.

@heading Misc.

@defvr {Setting} enable_mouse Enable Mouse Support
Enable mouse support in GNU Nano, allowing to use the mouse to perform actions
like select, copy or paste on the text.
@end defvr

@defvr {Setting} empty_space Have more space for editing
If enabled the whole available space will be availble for editing, no empty
lines beetwenn the text and minibar/status or help/shortcuts.
@end defvr

@defvr {Setting} rebind_delete Rebind delete keys
On some terminals it may be the delete keys don't properly work, in that case
let GNU Nano rebind them, to make them work.
@end defvr

@defvr {Setting} log_position Remember last position
When opening a file again, jump to the previous position.
@end defvr

@defvr {Setting} smart_home Enable smart home key
When Home is pressed anywhere but at the very beginning
of non-whitespace characters on a line, the cursor jumps to that beginning (either
forwards or backwards).  If the cursor  is  already at that position, it jumps
to the true beginning of the line.
@end defvr

@defvr {Setting} indicator Show scrollbar
Show scrollbar on the right side.
@end defvr

@defvr {Setting} save_onexit Auto save file on exit
Auto save file upon exit, without asking (disabled by default).
@end defvr

@defvr {Setting} trim_blanks Trim whitespace upon save
Trim whitespace upon save (disabled by default)
@end defvr